00:13:50.280 --> 00:13:51.780
So up on this board,
we were talking

00:13:51.780 --> 00:13:55.290
about what's the maximum energy
that a photon can transfer,

00:13:55.290 --> 00:13:57.750
which is always in the
back scattering case.

00:13:57.750 --> 00:14:00.630
The other part to note is
that that back scattering

00:14:00.630 --> 00:14:03.780
probability gets lower and
lower as the photon gets

00:14:03.780 --> 00:14:05.310
higher and higher in energy.

00:14:05.310 --> 00:14:06.600
Yeah.

00:14:06.600 --> 00:14:08.267
AUDIENCE: So it's
that basically saying,

00:14:08.267 --> 00:14:10.245
since we said forward
scattering [INAUDIBLE]

00:14:10.245 --> 00:14:11.998
as the energy gets
higher, you just

00:14:11.998 --> 00:14:15.872
have a harder chance
of it interacting.

00:14:15.872 --> 00:14:16.830
MICHAEL SHORT: Exactly.

00:14:16.830 --> 00:14:17.190
Yeah.

00:14:17.190 --> 00:14:18.815
The cross-section
value, well, yeah, it

00:14:18.815 --> 00:14:21.480
goes down as you
increase in energy.

00:14:21.480 --> 00:14:25.470
So a total forward scatter, if
you had a true forward scatter

00:14:25.470 --> 00:14:30.810
where theta equals 0,
I'll call that a miss.

00:14:30.810 --> 00:14:32.880
It means that, because
we saw on this formula

00:14:32.880 --> 00:14:39.840
up here when theta equals 0,
there is no energy transfer.

00:14:39.840 --> 00:14:41.040
Nothing.

00:14:41.040 --> 00:14:43.140
And so yeah, that would
be to me like a miss.

00:14:43.140 --> 00:14:45.140
If that angles ever
so slightly above 0,

00:14:45.140 --> 00:14:46.890
then there is some
scattering, but there's

00:14:46.890 --> 00:14:48.990
very little energy transfer.

00:14:48.990 --> 00:14:51.690
But that smaller
energy transfer becomes

00:14:51.690 --> 00:14:56.340
more likely when the photon
goes higher in energy.

00:14:56.340 --> 00:14:59.250
These are these sorts of
cause and effect relationships

00:14:59.250 --> 00:15:01.440
I want you guys to be
able to reason out.

00:15:01.440 --> 00:15:04.680
If I were to give you a polar
plot of this differential

00:15:04.680 --> 00:15:06.960
cross-section with
angle and energy,

00:15:06.960 --> 00:15:10.020
I'd want you to be able to
