00:15:30.880 --> 00:15:32.047
MICHAEL SHORT: That's right.

00:15:32.047 --> 00:15:35.680
Back scattering refers to the
photon going back, which means

00:15:35.680 --> 00:15:38.560
this situation,
where the difference

00:15:38.560 --> 00:15:41.290
in angle between the
incoming and outgoing photon

00:15:41.290 --> 00:15:44.470
is pi, 180 degrees, which means
it just turns around and moves

00:15:44.470 --> 00:15:45.490
the other way.

00:15:45.490 --> 00:15:46.960
Right.

00:15:46.960 --> 00:15:51.760
So that dashed line right
there would follow something

00:15:51.760 --> 00:15:54.310
like this at-- what did we say?

00:15:54.310 --> 00:15:55.720
0.2 MeV.

00:15:58.840 --> 00:16:01.480
The form, the full form of
this cross-section right

00:16:01.480 --> 00:16:04.540
here is referred to as the
Klein-Nishina cross-section.

00:16:04.540 --> 00:16:08.170
And it has been derived by
quantum electro dynamics, which

00:16:08.170 --> 00:16:10.180
I will not derive for you now.

00:16:10.180 --> 00:16:11.800
But there are plenty
of derivations

00:16:11.800 --> 00:16:14.088
online if that's
your kind of thing.

00:16:14.088 --> 00:16:15.880
And I had to make a
