00:46:58.175 --> 00:46:59.800
It's going to look
generally like this.

00:46:59.800 --> 00:47:03.500
There's going to be a
photoelectric region.

00:47:03.500 --> 00:47:05.000
Let's say that's
going to correspond

00:47:05.000 --> 00:47:07.370
to our photoelectric
cross-section, which goes

00:47:07.370 --> 00:47:09.560
way up with lower energies.

00:47:09.560 --> 00:47:14.070
There's going to be a pair
production part, which

00:47:14.070 --> 00:47:16.290
goes up with higher energies.

00:47:16.290 --> 00:47:20.130
And there's going to be this
kind of decreasing Compton

00:47:20.130 --> 00:47:21.720
